com.mousebird.maply

Class TileInfoNew

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.mousebird.maply.TileInfoNew
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    RemoteTileInfoNew, SimpleTileFetcher.SimpleTileInfo

    public class TileInfoNew
extends java.lang.Object
    TileInfo New Base class.
    This describes a single source of data tiles. A uses these to figure out what to load when and where. The loader passes the result of fetchInfoForTile to a TileFetcher to get the data it wants.

    • Field Detail

      • uniqueID

        public long uniqueID
        A unique ID used for sorting tile info objects when loading.

      • minZoom

        public int minZoom
        The minimum zoom level available. This is the lowest level we'll try to fetch. Any levels below that will be filled in with placeholders. Those are empty, but they allow us to load tiles beneath.

      • maxZoom

        public int maxZoom
        The maximum zoom level available. This is the highest level (e.g. largest) that we'll fetch for a given pyramid tile source. The source can sparse, so you are not required to have these tiles available, but this is as high as the loader will fetch.

    • Method Detail

      • fetchInfoForTile

        public java.lang.Object fetchInfoForTile(TileID tileID,
                                         boolean flipY)
        FetchInfo object for a given tile. The FetchInfo object is specific to the type of TileFetcher you're using and tells the fetcher how to get the data you wawnt. RemoteTileFetchers want a RemoteTileInfoNew object.
